A function is measurable iff the preimages of all left-closed intervals unbounded above are in the subspace sigma-algebra induced by its domain. The domain of ` F ` is required to be b subset of the underlying set of ` S ` . Definition 121C of [Fremlin1] p. 36, and Proposition 121B (iv) of [Fremlin1] p. 36 .
